		<marginalia anchor_text="FolgersHa2" hand="Italian" id="Ha2.075r_0001" marginalia_continues_from="Ha2.074v_0001" marginalia_from_transcription="Ha2.074v.xml">
			<language ident="LA">
				<position book_orientation="0" place="head">
					<marginalia_text>
						[[*2[v]]: Generales Professores, sine speciali praxi, aut certa
						necessariarum opum prouisione; moriuntur Mendici.
						Vt non modò Agrippa, et Turnebus, quanti philologi? =] = sed etiam Machiauellus, et Bodinus, quanti Politici?
						Tanti refert, solidè fundare rem familiarem: et a Teipso
							<!-- Continues from facing page, head, Ha2.074v -->
					</marginalia_text>
					<person name="Machiavelli"/>
					<person name="Jean Bodin"/>
				</position>
				<position book_orientation="0" place="right_margin">
					<marginalia_text>
						pendere: non ab amicis: qui nulli sunt egentibus.
						Contemnuntur pauperu[m] dignissimi: a[e]stimantur diuitu[m] indignissimi.
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>
				[[*2[v]]: General professors are without any special praxis or any particular foresight for necessary resources; they shall die poor.
				Is it not the same for Agrippa and Turnebus as philologists?] But even Machiavelli and Bodin, as Politicians?
				It is of much importance to build a solid foundation for the patrimony of your family and to depend
				on yourself, not on your friends, who need nothing. The worthiest of the poor are held in contempt,
				the unworthiest the wealthy are held in esteem.				
			</translation>
		</marginalia>
		
		
		<marginalia hand="Italian">
			<language ident="LA">
				<position book_orientation="0" place="tail">
					<marginalia_text>
						Prouidus est plenus: improuidus extat egenus.
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>
				He who is cautious is plentiful: he who lacks caution stands out as destitute.
			</translation>
		</marginalia>
		
		<marginalia hand="Italian">
			<language ident="LA">
				<position book_orientation="270" place="left_margin">
					<marginalia_text>
						Parum habet habilitatis, qui non potest vni abundè prouidere.
						Quid scit, qui nescit Seipsum adiuuare?
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>
				He who cannot fully guard against one thing has too little ability.
				He who does not know how to help himself, what can he know?
			</translation>
		</marginalia>
		
		
